# Python scripts

- Linters: `.venv-lint` via `make lint-python`
- Tests: `.venv-test` via `make test-scripts`
- Do not invoke black/pylint/mypy directly; use Makefile targets
- SPDX header on new files; trailing blank line after header block

## Modern Python (3.11+)

Project requires Python >=3.11. Match CONTRIBUTING Python style:

- Never add `from __future__ import annotations` (or any `__future__` import).
- Use built-in generics (`list[str]`, `dict[str, str]`) and PEP 604 unions
  (`str | None`); do not import `List`, `Optional`, `Union`, etc. from `typing`.
- Do not import from `typing_extensions` when the name is in stdlib `typing`
  on 3.11+ (e.g. `Self`, `Required`, `TypeVarTuple`).
- Violations fail `make lint-python` (checker: `scripts/python_modern_style.py`).
